This paper deals with natural language processing and information retrieval, which are core topics in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL). The paper's focus on extracting measured information from text is particularly relevant to information retrieval and natural language processing applications in scientific and technical domains, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
